@startuml
actor Student
participant "SubmissionService" as SubmissionService
participant "AuditService" as Audit
participant "ICryptoService" as Crypto
database DB
actor Lecturer
actor Admin

Student -> SubmissionService : submit verified or failed submission event
SubmissionService -> Audit : recordAudit(actionType, actor, entity, details)
Audit -> Audit : build canonical payload\n(actionType, actorUserId, entityType, entityId, timestamp, details)
Audit -> DB : load previous audit record integrity value (optional)
DB --> Audit : previousIntegrityValue
Audit -> Crypto : computeAuditMac(canonicalPayload + previousIntegrityValue, auditSecret)
Crypto --> Audit : integrityValue (HMAC-SHA-256)
Audit -> DB : append AuditLog\n+ integrityValue\n+ previousIntegrityValue
DB --> Audit : audit entry stored
Audit --> SubmissionService : audit recorded

Lecturer -> DB : review submission-related audit history
DB --> Lecturer : append-only audit events + integrity values
Admin -> DB : inspect sensitive action trail
DB --> Admin : audit evidence for investigation

note right of Audit
Pack 04 recommends HMAC-SHA-256 for the first
 audit-integrity pass because it provides
 authenticated integrity for internal records.
end note

note right of DB
No ordinary update path is assumed for AuditLog.
The model is append-oriented and can optionally
 chain previousIntegrityValue for stronger tamper evidence.
end note
@enduml

